We are proud to support the @vanvenrooyktmracing team for 2026 with handlebars and grips. The team has three riders competing in three different @mxgp categories:

 @mattguada101 #101 in MXGP
 @noelzanocz #716 in MX2
 @katona.aron39 #39 in EMX250

 Italian talent Mattia Guadagnini joins the team, bringing plenty of potential as he looks to make his mark at the top level.

 In the MX2 World Championship, Hungarian rider Noel Zanocz will step up from the EMX250 series. Zanocz will use his rookie MX2 season to gain experience and learn as much as possible as he adapts to the World Championship level.

 Completing the Van VVenrooy KTM line-up is another promising Hungarian, Áron Katona, who will move up to contest the EMX250 series in 2026. Katonais widely regarded as a talent to watch for the future, and the team are confident in his potential.

 HIT Link in Bio to see the full range of ODI Motocross products!

 #odigrips #odi #mx #mxgp #motocross #ODIFamily

