Q2 is a cruel mistress…
 @lukewayman1 0.4 off qualifying 😢 
 @charlie_hatton1 was looking so good until almost turning 180 degrees on himself which put him back too far to pull it back.
 Not long til Andorra next week 👀 

 We’ve got @george.madley.mtb in junior finals tomorrow so make sure you tune in 👂

The @gncc_racing Snowshoe Showdown was on right from the get-go where @codybarnes099 got a cracking start on his CRF250RX and shuffled into 2nd Place running down the mountain and there he would stay most of the race behind the other XC2 Rider who was running in 1st. Cody would fight valiantly, keeping it up on two and bringing home a strong 2nd Place in XC2 about seven seconds behind the leader and would earn 6th Place Overall.

 @mike_witkowski got a decent start battling for the top three in the XC1 Class aboard his CRF450RX and he would have a strong and consistent ride battling with the premier class elite. After a race long battle for the 4th–8th positions he would salvage 7th Place and 12th overall. 

 @_jojocunningham501 had a decent start in the top 4 in the 250 A Class and he would try his best to fight with the leader for an opportunity to overtake most the race, by the last lap, JoJo would be just a few seconds shy of victory coming home with 2nd Place in class and 19th Overall.

 @taylajones713 would make her return to racing, but again suffered an unfortunate event where a seemingly innocuous spill in the woods tuned into a tweaked knee as when picking up her motorcycle to remount she stepped on a log that rolled and was bad enough that she was unable to continue racing. The team is awaiting an update from Tayla after evaluations. 
 Either way we take the good with the bad and move forward. 
 Thanks for all the support!

 🎥: @ten4.media 
 #ridered #phxracing

