WOW! What a start to the 2024 FIM Enduro World Championship for the @hondaredmotoracing rider @steve_holcombe as he tastes victory in Portugal! 🏆

 The nine-time world champion, and defending EnduroGP champ, visited the podium on both days of round one in Portugal then won both the EnduroGP and Enduro1 classes on day two.

 Steve ended up top of the E1 standings and second in the EnduroGP, just two points from first spot.

 It was also an excellent weekend for the rest of the Honda Red Moto team riders: 

 @samuelebernardini321 ended the Portuguese GP with a double third step of the podium. Decisive and fast, on Sunday he also hit the top five in the EnduroGP, in a promising start to the season.

 @manolomorettini38 took 2nd place in the EJ1 class and the 3rd in the Junior Overall on Saturday, while on Sunday he finished 3rd, giving him fifth Overall.

 @nocerafrancesca116 had a tough Saturday (8th) but redeemed herself on Sunday as she took the third step on the podium. 

